Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.48,0:01:23.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是终极的前沿探险--太空环游 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is the ultimate frontier adventure, Space Travel
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.56,0:01:36.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但当你遨游在银河系的丛林中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But when trekking through the galactic jungles
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.90,0:01:40.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你必须留意宇宙中的热区 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One must steer clear of the cosmic, hot zones
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.42,0:01:44.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里充满了爆炸和陷阱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Places teeming with violence and intrigue.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.30,0:01:54.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些危险的地方爆发力很强 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are dangerous places certainly  very energetic phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.26,0:02:00.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发力比爆炸的原子弹还要强 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That are a lot more powerful than  atomic bombs being detonated
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.97,0:02:03.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量无限 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Infinitely more powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.74,0:02:09.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙似乎到处充满了爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe does seem to be a very violent place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.72,0:02:15.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,似乎它的诞生就源于爆炸 熟知的"大爆炸理论" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It seems to have been born in a  violent explosion called "The Big Bang"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.60,0:02:18.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且爆炸还在继续 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there is also violent processes going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.48,0:02:29.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2004年12月27日 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On december 27, 2004
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.81,0:02:37.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卫星录下了伟大的宇宙爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Satellites picked up the greatest cosmic  explosion ever recorded
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.72,0:02:43.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,三万光年以外的一次爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A blast 30,000 light-years away
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.54,0:02:48.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸威力可以轻易摧毁地球的外部大气层 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which had the power to briefly alter  our planet's upper atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.57,0:02:57.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸是由一颗磁星引起的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The blast was caused by a magnetar
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.29,0:03:02.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星是太空中最稠密 最危险之一的星星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The densest and one of the most  dangerous stars in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.67,0:03:06.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗磁星的磁场力约是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnetic field strength of a magnetar is about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.88,0:03:10.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球磁场力的千万亿倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A thousand trillion times the magnetic field energy of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.12,0:03:14.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拿刷卡做参照 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And for reference
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.08,0:03:17.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,刷卡将清除信用卡上的信息 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This would wipe the information off a credit card
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.42,0:03:21.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一动作在十万英里远的地方就能完成 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At a distance of about 100,000 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.02,0:03:24.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,十万英里差不多是距月球距离的一半 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, this distance is sort of half  the distance of the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.53,0:03:28.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从天文学角度来说 十万英里是很短的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it's very nearby by astronomical standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.44,0:03:37.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些淘气的星球拥有宇宙中最强的磁场 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These mischievous stars have the strongest magnetic field in the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.04,0:03:43.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在银河中被科学家们证实的磁星共12颗 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists have confirmed 12 of these  rare stars in our galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.61,0:03:45.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能会更多 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there may be more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.32,0:03:51.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加州理工的布莱恩·卡梅伦 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Caltech's Brian Cameron
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.95,0:03:55.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在银河中寻找这些陌生的星球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scans the milky way for these strange stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.13,0:04:07.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星是中子星的一个特殊类别 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Magnetars are a special class of neutron stars
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.74,0:04:10.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拥有极强的磁场 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With ultra strong magnetic fields
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.71,0:04:13.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙中最稠密的物质形式 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The densest form of matter in the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.24,0:04:18.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第一颗磁星被发现时 处于高能级状态 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first magnetar showed itself in  the form of a high-energy event
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.45,0:04:20.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发现于70年代晚期 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That was detected in the late'70s
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.28,0:04:21.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然那时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.12,0:04:23.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们并不知道那就是磁星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We didn't know that it was a magnetar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.05,0:04:25.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到90年代早期 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It wasn't until the early'90s
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.59,0:04:27.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,研究人员指出 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That researchers suggested that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.09,0:04:31.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些物体被磁场控制着 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these objects were dominated by magnetic fields
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.66,0:04:37.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而确立了磁星理论 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that the magnetar theory was actually confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.84,0:04:44.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星的形成基于超大行星的毁灭 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Magnetars are born out of the  death throes of massive stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.51,0:04:45.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当一颗星灭亡时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a star dies
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:50.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它开始瓦解形成超新星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It begins to collapse and go supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.25,0:04:52.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时超新星的爆炸中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sometimes, a dense neutron star
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.65,0:04:56.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会形成密集的中子星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Forms from the centers of that supernova explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.92,0:04:59.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一过程中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During the process
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.12,0:05:02.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些中子星变成了磁星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A few neutron stars become magnetars
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.49,0:05:06.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拥有极强的磁场 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which possess a strong magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.06,0:05:11.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些行星放射出高能的X射线和伽马射线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These stars eject high-energy emissions  of x-rays and gamma rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.80,0:05:16.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为一般的中子星诞生于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We think that normal neutron stars are born from regular stars
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.74,0:05:19.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那种比太阳质量大10或20倍的正规星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That are something like 10 or 20 times the mass of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.81,0:05:20.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但有证据显示 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there's evidence that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.78,0:05:24.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星更有可能诞生于甚至更大的行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}magnetars are born from possibly even more massive stars
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.11,0:05:27.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那种比太阳质量大40倍的行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Than this, something like 40 times the mass of the S un.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.02,0:05:29.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很明显 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Typically
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.79,0:05:34.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这么大质量的行星太重而不易形成中子星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A star of such mass would be  too heavy to form a neutron star.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.59,0:05:40.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相反它的质量将陷入黑洞中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead, its mass would collapse into a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.00,0:05:42.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞的形成就是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes are formed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.93,0:05:46.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把一定数目的质量填入一定的体积中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From cramming a certain amount  of mass in a certain volume.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.17,0:05:47.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无论如何\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And for whatever reason
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.37,0:05:50.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些质量超大的行星 没有形成中子星的能力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These stars are unable to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.87,0:05:53.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有个理论认为一些超大行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One theory is that some massive stars
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:57.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在爆炸为超新星前 经历失重过程 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Undergo a weight loss program right  before exploding as a supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.88,0:05:59.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,损失了90%的质量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Losing 90 percent of their mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.05,0:06:03.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就无法陷入黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So instead of collapsing into a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.42,0:06:06.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,余下的部分变成了中子星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The emaciated star becomes a neutron star
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.09,0:06:09.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拥有超强磁力的中子星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With extreme magnetic powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.46,0:06:14.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当磁力变得太强时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the magnetic force gets incredibly strong
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.23,0:06:17.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使磁星地面变形 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It deforms the magnetar's crust
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.57,0:06:24.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在它表面产生地震叫做"星震" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Creating seismic events called "starquakes" on its surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.54,0:06:29.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终如果地表在压力下破裂 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eventually, if this crust breaks under the stress
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.68,0:06:33.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁场使它进入低能状态 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the magnetic field reconfigures  itself into a lower energy state
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.65,0:06:34.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当这些发生时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when this happens
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.92,0:06:39.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发出了火球 飞离星球边缘 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A fireball is launched off the side of the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.13,0:06:45.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以 我们认为中子星表面的星震\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So starquakes on neutron stars' surfaces are thought to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.87,0:06:49.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生了我们看见这些巨大的火焰 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}give rise to these giant flares that we see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.50,0:06:56.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星出现这些火焰后 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After a magnetar undergoes one of these flares
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.61,0:06:59.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比银河里所有星星都要亮 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It outshines all the stars in the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.84,0:07:04.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火焰将持续仅十分之一秒 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For a few--For the few tenths of  a second that it's taking place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.65,0:07:08.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的火焰里是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Within these giant flares
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.52,0:07:14.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以光速传播的伽马射线的短暂爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Are short bursts of gamma rays,  which move at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.16,0:07:19.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自磁星的巨大火焰就是伽马射线爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The giant flares from magnetars are gamma ray bursts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.16,0:07:21.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们持续不久 不到一秒钟 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're very short in duration, Less than a second
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.36,0:07:24.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比起其他伽马射线爆炸来说 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And have very hard x-ray spectra
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.07,0:07:27.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的X射线光谱很固定 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Compared to another class of gamma ray bursts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.31,0:07:33.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果太空漫游者偏离了航线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If a deep space traveler veered off course
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.04,0:07:34.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不幸遇到超大行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And was unlucky enough
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.08,0:07:38.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绕过它则需要700英里路程 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To pass within 700 miles of one of these massive objects
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.28,0:07:41.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,结果是很恐怖的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The consequences would be horrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.02,0:07:46.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnetic field of the magnetar
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.19,0:07:49.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能毫不夸张地扭曲人体内的原子 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Can literally warp the atoms in human flesh
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:52.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的引力能将一个人撕碎 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And its gravitational forces would tear a person apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.17,0:08:01.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么太阳系中一颗磁星将何时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So then, how close would a magnetar have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.30,0:08:04.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引发大灾难呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To wreak havoc in our solar system?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.18,0:08:08.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有人认为 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some suggest
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.05,0:08:12.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就算19光年远的一颗磁星爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That a blast from a magnetar even 10 light-years away
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.95,0:08:15.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也将引起宇宙混乱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could produce cosmic chaos
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.05,0:08:17.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将会破坏我们的臭氧层 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That would destroy our ozone layer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.32,0:08:20.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,导致大量生物灭绝 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And cause mass extinctions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.76,0:08:24.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但你知道那样发生的几率很小 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The chances of that happening are so low that, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.76,0:08:26.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎是不可能的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're completely implausible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.66,0:08:27.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种几率与\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be no different than
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.83,0:08:30.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正规星穿过太阳系一样不太可能 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a regular star passing through the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.57,0:08:31.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道正规星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we know that a regular star
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.83,0:08:34.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自太阳系形成以来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Has not passed through the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.24,0:08:37.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就从没进入过太阳系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since this solar system was formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.88,0:08:44.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家认为 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists think
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.68,0:08:48.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星寿命只有几千年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That magnetars are only a few thousand years old
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.02,0:08:52.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一万年后它们会变暗淡 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And will become dim after 10,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.66,0:08:57.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在才刚开始了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're just now starting to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.13,0:08:59.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星的生命周期 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The life cycle of magnetars.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.96,0:09:01.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为它们还很年轻 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We think that they're very young
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.66,0:09:05.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但具体有多年轻还不知道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how young is still uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.95,0:09:22.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除磁星之外 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In addition to magnetars
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.65,0:09:25.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过卫星和地面观察站\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Satellites and ground-based observatories
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.39,0:09:29.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人们还发现了 在太空中还有其它火爆的星球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Have been picking up other violent things in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.66,0:09:34.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们现已确定 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists have now confirmed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.13,0:09:37.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种幻影般的力量存在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The existence of a phantom-like force
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.90,0:09:40.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且很强大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's so strong
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.44,0:09:46.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这有可能是宇宙中最邪恶的现象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That it might very well be the most vicious phenomenon in the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.32,0:10:00.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鬼祟的这种力量萦绕于每个星系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stealthy villains haunt each and every galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.80,0:10:08.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就像野兽般把途经的星球撕碎 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One particular beast tears up anything in its path
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.80,0:10:12.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并把星球吞并 就像吃开胃小菜 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And gobbles it down like a cocktail hors d'oeuvre.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.31,0:10:17.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是宇宙中最怪异 最具破坏性的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's one of the most bizarre and destructive phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.48,0:10:19.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现象之一 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.41,0:10:21.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.15,0:10:26.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我认为黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.82,0:10:31.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是宇宙中力量最强大的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is the place which is more violent than anywhere else in our Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.33,0:10:36.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像走到了世界尽头 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's like going over the edge
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.86,0:10:39.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无回头之路 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you can't get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.76,0:10:42.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得是种致命的吸引 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's fatal attraction, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.41,0:10:50.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙中的黑洞处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A black hole is a region of space
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.71,0:10:53.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地心引力非常大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where the pull of gravity is so immense
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.55,0:10:58.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么的逃不掉 就连光也逃不掉 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That nothing can escape it not even light.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.06,0:11:08.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天体 物理 运动三项全能的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astrophysicist and triathlete
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.06,0:11:10.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,费约·奥济尔 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Feryal Ozel
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.56,0:11:11.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尝试去解决\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is attempting to unlock
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.90,0:11:16.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞引力周围的谜团 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The mysteries surrounding this elusive cosmic force.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.51,0:11:23.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.44,0:11:25.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引力太强大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gravity is so strong
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.84,0:11:28.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有其他力能竞争得过它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That no other force can compete with it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.58,0:11:31.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,任何物质都缩解为单个点 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So everything collapses to a single point.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.02,0:11:35.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奥济尔说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ozel says
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.89,0:11:38.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只要靠近黑洞 无论什么东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whatever has a close encounter with a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.66,0:11:43.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都会成为潮汐般引力的牺牲品 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Will fall victim to its relentless tidal force of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.50,0:11:50.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一下你在游泳池里游泳 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine you're swimming in a pool
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.07,0:11:52.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有水流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there is no current
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.57,0:11:56.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以随意向哪个方向游 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can go whichever direction you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.01,0:12:03.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在假设你不在游泳池里游泳 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, imagine, you're taken out of this pool
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.32,0:12:05.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是在河里游泳 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you're in a river.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.12,0:12:10.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一下河中水流非常强 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine a current that is much, much, much stronger
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.36,0:12:12.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你只能朝一个方向运动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That the only direction that you could go
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.59,0:12:14.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是水流方向 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Would be with this current.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.09,0:12:20.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太空中黑洞附近地方 就类似于这条奔流的河 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The space around a black hole acts like this wild river.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.17,0:12:26.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你摆脱不了这股强大的拖力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You could never fight this enormous drag that you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.21,0:12:35.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当一个物体接近黑洞边缘时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As an object approaches the edge of a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.55,0:12:37.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞边缘叫做"视界" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Called the "event horizon,"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.15,0:12:39.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是不归路的临界点 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It reaches the point of no return.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.22,0:12:45.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随你离"视界"越来越近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As you come closer and closer to this event horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.96,0:12:47.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就越靠近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You would already be approaching
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.26,0:12:51.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太空这种极快的运动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This extremely fast motion of space under you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.90,0:12:55.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接下来你唯一的移动方向就是进入黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And your only future direction is now into the black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.41,0:13:04.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于黑洞本身 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The idea of the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.78,0:13:07.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,作为一个洞有时令人有点费解 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a hole sometimes can be a little bit confusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.61,0:13:08.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它究竟是什么 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What it really is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.75,0:13:09.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,某种意义上说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In some sense
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.61,0:13:13.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是一个你永远也回不来的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a place from which you can't return
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.35,0:13:16.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至少不是以你进入的方式回来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or at least, not in the form in which you went in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.43,0:13:26.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞难以发现 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes are difficult to detect
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.87,0:13:29.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为就像这名字暗示的一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because as the name suggests
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.20,0:13:33.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看不见它 因为它是黑暗的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You cannot see one by itself because it's black.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.74,0:13:35.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但科学家们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.51,0:13:37.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已发现一个黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Have spotted a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.21,0:13:40.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在它侵蚀太空中其它物质的时候 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When its gravity affects something else in space
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.25,0:13:42.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如侵吞一颗路过的行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Such as a passing star.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.62,0:13:50.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个完全隔绝的黑洞是无法看见的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A completely isolated black hole would not be visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.42,0:13:53.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从黑洞那我们真正看到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we really see from a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.46,0:13:57.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际是黑洞周围盘旋的强放射性物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is actually the hot material that's swirling around it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.76,0:14:00.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正被吸入其中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's being sucked into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.93,0:14:05.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这些强力的黑洞附近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, in the neighborhood of these powerful black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.77,0:14:06.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会发现许多辐射 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You'll get a lot of radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.97,0:14:08.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,辐射的产生由于黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Resulting from the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.57,0:14:12.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吸入物质 拉伸它 绞曲它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pulling in material - And stretching it - And twisting it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:14.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,辐射就发生在物质坠入黑洞过程中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As it's falling in black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.85,0:14:20.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞侵食着近距离的所有物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes consuming anything in close range
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.25,0:14:25.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且有几十亿以上的黑洞潜伏于宇宙中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there are billions upon billions of them prowling the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.13,0:14:36.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天体物理学家安德里亚·盖兹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astrophysicist Andrea Ghez
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.23,0:14:40.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是世界主要黑洞猎手之一 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is one of the world's leading black hole hunters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.48,0:14:44.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞并不挑食 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes are not picky eaters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.84,0:14:47.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,见一个吃一个 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They'll dine on whatever get nearby
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.58,0:14:49.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们很乐意吞气体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So they will happily eat gas
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.75,0:14:53.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们也很乐意吞并一颗恒星或行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They will happily consume a star or a planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.02,0:14:57.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它吸食一个行星时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a black hole dines on a star
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.06,0:15:00.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不会先把它撕碎 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It does so first by tearing it apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.09,0:15:04.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以想象成软软的油灰被拉伸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you might think of silly putty being stretched out
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.20,0:15:06.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后流动在水似的物体上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then it just streams on in sort of like water
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.97,0:15:09.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着被慢慢卷入 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Going down a drain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.07,0:15:11.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全就像磨面粉 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's completely pulverized.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.18,0:15:20.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为黑洞的产生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes are produced, we believe
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.51,0:15:23.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是由于超大恒星的瓦解 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By the collapse of the core of a massive star
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.88,0:15:27.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那种比太阳质量大25~30倍的恒星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something like 25 or 30 times the mass of the Sun or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.32,0:15:31.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当恒星的生命快结束时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it comes to the end of its lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.69,0:15:33.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超大恒星的地心开始燃烧 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A massive star burns its core
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.99,0:15:36.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一直烧掉氦 碳 氮 氧 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the way past helium, carbon, nitrogen, oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.03,0:15:41.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,烧到最后只剩没有核能的铁 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the way to iron which has no more nuclear fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.30,0:15:44.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当铁心重建出一块物质时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when that iron core builds up to a certain mass
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.54,0:15:49.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会出现它自身无法再支撑的一点 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There comes a point where it can no longer support itself
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.24,0:15:51.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这时铁心崩溃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the core will collapse
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.38,0:15:53.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到形成黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the way to a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.08,0:15:57.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时形成一颗超新星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Producing at the same time a supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.19,0:16:05.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超新星传送出超大能量的爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The supernova sends out explosive amounts of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.16,0:16:08.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以超新星附近的物质将成灰烬 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So anything in its vicinity will get obliterated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.43,0:16:11.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后爆炸后的残迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then, the remnants of the explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.40,0:16:14.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,坠入新形成的黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fall into a newly formed black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.77,0:16:17.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,似乎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it seems
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.54,0:16:20.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞吸引的关键在于向心引力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The key to the black holes' allure is gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.18,0:16:25.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向心引力把物质拉聚在一起 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity will pull things around
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.34,0:16:29.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像太阳把各大行星拉聚在一起一样 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just like the Sun's gravity pulls the planets around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.71,0:16:30.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.75,0:16:33.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,行星的大部分时光都是绕黑洞轨道和陆地飞行 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars will happily orbit the black hole for most of its life
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.02,0:16:35.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而不会被吸入其中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And won't actually be sucked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.99,0:16:37.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些行星实际很安全 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These stars are actually safe
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.56,0:16:40.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会被黑洞吸引而脱离轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From the fatal attraction of the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.69,0:16:42.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但如果你要大胆靠近的话 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if you do venture too close
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:45.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常接近黑洞边缘 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like extremely close to the edge
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.26,0:16:48.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就会被吸入其中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then you do get sucked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.17,0:16:52.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家认为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists believe there are
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.64,0:16:57.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们银河系中 存在难捉摸的黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Millions of wayward black holes throughout our galaxy, the milky way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.24,0:17:02.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们不能够看见它们 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And because we can't readily see them
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.11,0:17:05.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能附近就有一个 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One could be right next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.72,0:17:10.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么到底离黑洞多近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So how close does something have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.19,0:17:13.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们就会被吸入其中呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To get sucked into a black hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.49,0:17:17.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离黑洞约地球到太阳间距离这么远 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Too close to a black hole is about the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:20.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就算很近了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Between the sun and the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.23,0:17:23.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但那确实太近了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that is certainly too close.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.34,0:17:29.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对未来太空旅行者死于黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For future space travelers, death by a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.81,0:17:32.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会是种壮烈的死法 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Would be a violent way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.92,0:17:40.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞杀死你的方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The method by which a black hole could kill you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.55,0:17:43.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,取决于黑洞有多大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Depends on how big the black hole is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.26,0:17:49.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞分两类 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They come in two categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.09,0:17:52.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们大部分是呈星状的黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of them are the stellar-mass black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.60,0:17:56.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,质量是太阳的5~30倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which are five to 30 times the mass of our sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.90,0:18:01.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果是星状的黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the black hole is stellar-sized
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.81,0:18:04.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞周围潮汐般的力量大得足以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then the tidal forces near the black hole is strong enough
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.01,0:18:07.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把你整齐地撕裂 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That it will tear you apart tidily
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.71,0:18:10.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至在视界以外 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even well outside the event horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.22,0:18:11.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就算你想坠入黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you wanted to fall into a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:14.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你一定不会想坠入这一种黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You certainly wouldn't want to fall into one of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.59,0:18:16.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它将把你撕成面条 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will spaghettify you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.43,0:18:23.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但除了星状黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in addition to the stellar-sized black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.06,0:18:25.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有一种庞大黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are others that are mammoth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.23,0:18:29.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是太阳质量的百万至十亿倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Millions to a billion times the mass of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.20,0:18:33.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在科学家们相信\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And now, scientists believe
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.81,0:18:40.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种庞然大物占据着每个星系的中央位置 银河系也是 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That these monsters hold center court in every galaxy including our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.32,0:18:51.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.35,0:18:51.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're one
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.84,0:18:56.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太空中最神秘 最具潜在危险的奇物之一 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of the most mysterious and potentially dangerous oddities in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.20,0:19:02.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个黑洞胃口非常大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A black hole has a ravenous appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.03,0:19:04.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吞食途经的任何物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It sucks in everything in its path
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.67,0:19:08.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吐出残渣 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And spits out what it doesn't devour.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.07,0:19:13.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在科学家们发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And now, scientists have discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.11,0:19:15.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,存在超大质量黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are supermassive black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.65,0:19:20.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比它同族的星状黑洞要大百万倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which are millions of times bigger than their stellar mass cousins.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.22,0:19:29.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,证据显示\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And evidence suggests
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.63,0:19:34.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超大质量黑洞诞生于宇宙大爆炸之后 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That supermassive black holes were born after the big bang
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.20,0:19:37.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生于宇宙之初 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Universe was first created.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.37,0:19:43.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的形成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The leading idea is that they would have formed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.41,0:19:45.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像超大行星瓦解形成的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just like the stellar black holes from the collapse
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.58,0:19:48.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星状黑洞的形成一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of the core of a massive star.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.38,0:19:53.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们会长大 依靠吸食\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But then they grew by feeding grossly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.15,0:19:58.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与它们相撞的其他星系的气体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From the gas from other galaxies which collided with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.56,0:20:10.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们发现 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists have discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.37,0:20:11.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些黑色怪物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That these black ogres
