Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.37,0:38:11.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果银河系与仙女系的真的发生的话 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If that really happens in the case of the Milky Way and Andromeda
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.27,0:38:11.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可能会产生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We could have
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.94,0:38:15.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个类星体活跃在合并星系的中心 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For a period of some tens, even a hundred million years
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.91,0:38:18.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,持续几千万年甚至一亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A quasar active in the center of the merged galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.08,0:38:22.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体产出的能量约是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a quasar puts out about a hundred times
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.22,0:38:24.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个普通星系的一百倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As much energy as a typical galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.79,0:38:27.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们被卷入一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if we were actually thrown into an orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.69,0:38:29.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带我们飞向星系中心的轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which took us towards the center of the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.89,0:38:32.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们就可能近距离接近类星体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We could get very close to that quasar
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.29,0:38:34.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然我们也会被烧焦 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And really get scorched.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.33,0:38:40.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"类星体"这个词含义是"类似恒星的射电源" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The word "quasar" stands for "quasistellar radio source,"
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.47,0:38:45.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,意思是: 类似恒星的无线电波发射源 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which means star-like emitters of radio waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.48,0:38:48.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当类星体现象还是一个谜的时候 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The word was coined
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.18,0:38:50.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才创造了这个词 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the quasar phenomena was still a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.51,0:38:56.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们知道它们一点也不像恒星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, we know they're not star-like at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.62,0:39:01.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除了放射无线电波和可见光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In addition to emitting radio waves and visible light
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.19,0:39:04.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体还发出紫外线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Quasars also give off ultraviolet rays
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.76,0:39:11.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红外线 X射线 伽马射线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Infrared waves, x-rays, and gamma rays
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.61,0:39:21.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果某物或某人靠得太近 将造成致命伤害 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All deadlylf, something or someone gets too close.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.01,0:39:29.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体是一个很远的超大质量黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A quasar is a supermassive black hole at large distance
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.92,0:39:33.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但很活跃充满能量散发光芒 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's is active, it's powerful, it's emitting light
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.42,0:39:36.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以在很多波带上发现它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we can observe it in many wave bands.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.66,0:39:41.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体第一次被发现是在1960年代 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Quasars were first discovered in the 1960s
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.00,0:39:44.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但随着射电成像望远镜的技术日趋成熟 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But as radio telescope imaging got better
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.97,0:39:47.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家发现有的类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers discovered that some of those quasars
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.40,0:39:51.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也有强大的喷射光束 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Also have powerful jets beaming out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.77,0:39:57.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种类星体叫做"耀类星体" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These particular quasars are called "blazars"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.05,0:40:01.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许是宇宙中最激烈的现象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Probably some of the most violent phenomena in the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.39,0:40:10.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耀类星体跟类星体一样 靠黑洞提供能源 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Blazars are powered by black holes just like quasars.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.09,0:40:12.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是能量的分配有所不同 耀类星体的所有能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But they're somewhat different in that all their energy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.63,0:40:13.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是集中到一起 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is being focused
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.66,0:40:17.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或是大部分能量集中在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or a large amount of their energy is being focused into
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.15,0:40:19.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷射光束上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}jets which are streaming out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.80,0:40:24.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耀类星体的高能等离子体喷柱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A blazar's aggressive plasma jets produce
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.87,0:40:27.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生的无线电波辐射 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}radiation in the form of radio waves
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.41,0:40:29.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射频频谱从低一直高到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the way through the spectrum
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.11,0:40:31.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高能的伽马射线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Up to high-energy gamma rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.79,0:40:38.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天体物理学家格林·派勒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astrophysicist Glenn Piner
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.72,0:40:41.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曾调查过这些外来星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Had been investigating the physical conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.16,0:40:43.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中心的实际情况 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the centers of these exotic galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.13,0:40:52.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以用这口喷泉来比拟耀类星体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can use this fountain to visualize the geometry of a blazar.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.50,0:40:54.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果把喷泉的圆底座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If that circular base of the fountain
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.54,0:40:56.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比作类星体圆盘 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Represents the accretion disc
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.57,0:40:58.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么喷上来的水柱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then the jet of water that's coming up
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.81,0:41:03.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就代表来自类星体的等离子体喷柱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Represents the jet of plasma coming out from the blazar.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.35,0:41:07.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果地球沿着喷水方向移动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if the earth is sitting up in the direction that water is going
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.82,0:41:11.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么我们可以把它看成一个耀类星体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then we would see this object as a blazar.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.52,0:41:16.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对天文学家来说 它看起来就像看一个火光四射的长管 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For an astronomer, it's like looking down a fire hose.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.99,0:41:19.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看见它就会灼伤你的眼睛 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It really gets you in the eye to see this bright
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.90,0:41:23.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以名叫"耀类星体" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Blazing thing that we call a "blazar."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.00,0:41:29.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耀类星体喷射移动得异常快 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These blazar jets move exceptionally fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.57,0:41:35.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曾发现最快的能达到光速的99.9% \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The fastest observed move at 99.9 percent the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.28,0:41:39.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你拿着一个小东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you were to take a small object
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.82,0:41:41.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像这个保龄球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like this bowling ball
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.05,0:41:42.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想把它加速到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you wanted to accelerate it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.05,0:41:45.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,99.9%的光速 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Up to 99.9 percent of the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.35,0:41:46.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你将不得不把全地球产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You would have to give this bowling ball
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.92,0:41:48.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,全用在这个保龄球上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the energy produced in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.79,0:41:52.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要保持一周才能达到99.9%的光速 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For an entire week to accelerate it to that speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.80,0:42:01.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这些耀类星体里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in these blazars
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.97,0:42:04.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不仅要把像保龄球样的小东西加速 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're accelerating not just small objects like bowling balls
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.71,0:42:07.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且还要将像木星之类大质量的或者比木星质量还大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But large masses of the mass of the planet jupiter or larger
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.91,0:42:08.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加速到那个速度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To those speeds
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.94,0:42:10.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那这个高效的引擎需给它们施加\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So they're being given incredible amounts of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.85,0:42:13.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,偌大的能量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By this efficient engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.65,0:42:18.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耀类星体会对靠近它们喷射柱的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Blazars pose unimaginable consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.68,0:42:22.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,造成难以想象的结果 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To cosmic objects that get too close to its deadly jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.39,0:42:26.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果有个行星靠得比较近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If there was a planet relatively close
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.66,0:42:29.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离实际喷射柱几光年远 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A few light-years from the actual jet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.53,0:42:30.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耀类星体对这个行星的辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The radiation on that planet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.80,0:42:34.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能是附近恒星对它辐射的百万倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could be millions of times what it gets from the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.30,0:42:37.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它将长期曝露于高辐射环境下 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be continually exposed to high levels of radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.27,0:42:38.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我认为 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So I don't think
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.27,0:42:40.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想在行星上寻找生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We wanna look for life on a planet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.54,0:42:44.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就不应在环绕耀类星体喷柱运行的行星上找 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That would be orbiting a star, that's in a blazar jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.42,0:42:50.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们把全球的射电望远镜连在一起 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists link radio telescopes all over the world
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.62,0:42:55.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以达到放大耀类星体喷柱的效果 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To achieve the magnification needed to zoom in on a blazar jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.93,0:42:59.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给你打个这种放大的类比 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So to give you an analogy for what kind of magnification
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.46,0:43:03.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种放大效果可以在洛杉矶阅读\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That would be magnification sufficient to read a newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.63,0:43:07.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在纽约某人手中拿着的报纸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That someone was holding in New York from Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.17,0:43:11.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们希望尽可能的观测到星系中央黑洞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We'd love to look as close to the central black hole as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.41,0:43:13.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那样我们才能得知它们是怎么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we could actually figure out how nature
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.11,0:43:14.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加速喷柱的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is accelerating these jets
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.08,0:43:16.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怎么使它们达到高速的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And getting them up to such high speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.68,0:43:19.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们也想知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we'd also like to know
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.35,0:43:21.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些喷柱实际是由什么构成的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What it is actually that the jets are made of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.82,0:43:23.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为那种构成成分证明是某种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because it turns out that's something
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.45,0:43:26.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目前未知的东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's currently not known.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.16,0:43:31.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有待去发掘耀类星体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until more is known about blazars
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.66,0:43:34.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家会在邻近地区关注它们 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers will keep a neighborhood watch for them
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.73,0:43:36.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,关注我们未知宇宙中的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As well as all the other dangerous places
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.90,0:43:39.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有其它那些危险的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In our uncontrollable Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.51,0:43:43.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以肯定的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Definitely
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.87,0:43:46.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙中的爆发事件从来没停过 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are violent events going on in the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.48,0:43:51.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,释放的能量大到超出我们的想象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Much, much more energy than we can even imagine on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.21,0:43:56.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比太阳亮万亿倍的光芒突然闪现 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are trillions of suns shining all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.55,0:43:59.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些就是我们谈论着的能量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those are the kinds of energies that we're talking about.
